179	
180	### Football modeling logic (what to implement)
181	- **Poisson goal model:** goals ~ Poisson(λ), λ = f(attack_i, defence_j, home_adv); predict scoreline → W/D/L.
182	- **Dixon-Coles:** add `rho` low-score correction + exponential time-decay (recent matches weigh more).
183	- **Elo / World Football Elo:** rating updated by result × margin × importance; Elo-diff → win prob.
184	- **Groll hybrid:** feed time-weighted Poisson abilities + Elo + covariates into a Random Forest /
185	  gradient boosting — beats either component alone (arXiv 1806.03208).
186	- **Why goal-based ≫ the old classifier:** keeps goal margin → enables group goal-difference tiebreaks,
187	  models draws, simulates any matchup. A win/loss classifier cannot produce tournament standings.
188	- **Neutral venue:** WC2026 host cities are neutral → `home_advantage = 0` for neutral matches.
189	- **Draws:** group = W/D/L + goal-diff; knockout = extra time (`λ×0.33`) then penalty coin-flip.
190	- **Bookmaker odds:** the benchmark to beat (de-vig consensus). Here used only for evaluation.
191	- **Monte Carlo:** condition on played results → simulate the rest → repeat ~100k → title odds.
192	
193	### Prior work (reference methods)
194	- Groll/Ley/Schauberger/Van Eetvelde hybrid RF — arXiv 1806.03208; reproduced for WC2022/2026.
195	- Leitner-Zeileis-Hornik bookmaker consensus — predicted 2010 winner + 3/4 of 2014 semifinalists.
196	- Dixon-Coles 1997 (JRSS C 46(2):265–280) — foundational goal model.
197	- Robberechts-Davis (KU Leuven) — Elo-diff ordered logit best 2002–2014 (acc 0.5938, RPS 0.1860).
198	- Egidi-Torelli — double Poisson beat result-classifiers on Brier (small sample, inconclusive).
199	
200	### Data stack (no-key training; key only for live)
201	- **martj42/international_results** (CC0) — all international matches 1872→present. **Primary training.**
202	- **football-data.org** (key in `.env`) — live WC2026 standings/results/remaining fixtures only.
203	- **eloratings.net** / computed Elo — World Football Elo features.
204	- **FIFA rankings** (Kaggle cnc8/cashncarry) — ranking feature.
205	- Historical WC **odds scraped** (2014/18/22) — backtest baseline only.
206	
207	### Caveats
208	- Literature metric wins are small-sample (Egidi-Torelli Brier edge = 16 matches; inconclusive).
209	- WC2026 mostly neutral venues → standard home-advantage does not apply.
210	- WC2026 hybrid result is a June 2026 blog reproduction, not peer-reviewed.
211	- `0.33` extra-time multiplier + coin-flip shootout are implementation choices, not standards.
212	- Odds/Elo scrapers are fragile — cache and degrade gracefully; verify licensing before shipping.
213	
214	### Sources
215	arXiv 1806.03208 · zeileis.org/news/fifa2022 · r-bloggers WC2026 (2026-06) · Dixon-Coles JRSS C
216	(1467-9876.00065) · ideas.repec.org/p/inn/wpaper/2018-09 · leoegidi.github.io egidi_comparing ·
217	KU Leuven Robberechts-Davis · github.com/opisthokonta/goalmodel · dashee87.github.io Dixon-Coles ·
218	pena.lt/y Dixon-Coles · Kaggle sslp23 FIFA2022 · github.com/martj42/international_results ·
219	eloratings.net · football-data.co.uk · github.com/probberechts/soccerdata · github.com/statsbomb/open-data
