2026-06-23 21:04:38,660 DEBUG msg #11: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_01M1hcq3hMSJpbTpNkRAHQXu): {"assignees":[{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwOTUyOTQ4","login":"SilvioBaratto","name":"Silvio Angelo Baratto Roldan","databaseId":0}],"body":"## Goal\nAdd a pure-function team-name normalization module so live football-data.org results and martj42 historical results join on a single canonical country name. This is the shared foundation both data loaders (martj42 + live) depend on — build it first.\n\n## Context\nmartj42 and football-data.org spell several nations differently and a later cycle must inner-join live `played` results onto martj42 history on `HOME_TEAM`/`AWAY_TEAM`. Known divergences from the data contract: `Türkiye`/`Turkey`, `Czechia`, `South Korea`/`Korea Republic`/`Republic of Korea`, `United States`/`USA`/`United States of America`, `IR Iran`/`Iran`, `China PR`/`China`.\n\nCodebase conventions to follow (from `worldcup_playoff/data/`):\n- Every module opens with a `\"\"\"docstring\"\"\"`, then `from __future__ import annotations`, then `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`.\n- `pandas` is available; this module needs `pandas` only — **no I/O, no network**, so it is trivially unit-testable and is a leaf dependency (avoids any import cycle between `martj42_loader.py` and `live.py`).\n- Package exports live in `worldcup_playoff/data/__init__.py` (imports + `__all__`); additions there are purely additive.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `normalize_team(name: str) -> str` strips/collapses whitespace, looks up a case-insensitive alias map, and falls back to the cleaned input for unknown names (< 10 lines)\n- [ ] `CANONICAL_NAMES: dict[str, str]` covers every alias in the data contract (`Türkiye→Turkey`, `Czechia`, `South Korea`, `United States`/`USA`, `IR Iran`, `China PR`, etc.); lookup is case- and whitespace-insensitive\n- [ ] `normalize_series(s: pd.Series) -> pd.Series` is vectorized (`.map`), preserves length and index\n- [ ] Idempotence: `normalize_team(canonical) == canonical` for every canonical value\n- [ ] New symbols exported from `worldcup_playoff/data/__init__.py` (`normalize_team`, `normalize_series`, `CANONICAL_NAMES`) and added to `__all__`\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- None\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/data/crosswalk.py` — `CANONICAL_NAMES` alias map, `normalize_team`, `normalize_series`, optional `is_known(name) -> bool` for diagnostics. Keep keys lowercased+stripped at lookup time so the dict stays compact.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_crosswalk.py` — pure unit tests, no I/O. Parametrize over alias→canonical pairs; assert unknown names pass through cleaned; assert `normalize_series` preserves length/index; one idempotence round-trip test.\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/data/__init__.py` — add the three exports and extend `__all__`.\n- Pure functions only; do **not** import `FootballClient`, `pandas` I/O, or any other data module here — this module must remain a leaf so the loaders can both depend on it without cycles.","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIFhg","name":"priority:high","description":"High priority","color":"FF0000"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopII0g","name":"phase:implement","description":"Phase: implement","color":"D4C5F9"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIKMQ","name":"agent:python-pro","description":"Agent: python-pro","color":"7057FF"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopKxrQ","name":"area:data","description":"Area: data","color":"0052CC"}],"milestone":{"number":1,"title":"Cycle 1 — Data Loaders & Normalization","description":"Load martj42 CC0 international results (no-key primary source); live WC2026 adapter for football-data.org standings/results/fixtures; team-name normalization crosswalk (martj42 ↔ API); WC2026 Round-of-32 bracket-slotting rules (top 2 per group + 8 best 3rds → knockout template). Verify exact schemas match the data contracts (49,477 martj42 rows, 104 WC2026 matches). All loaders must be no-key by default (key optional for live state only).","dueOn":null},"state":"OPEN","title":"feat: team-name crosswalk for martj42 ↔ football-data.org normalization"}
