2026-06-23 21:27:19,885 DEBUG msg #12: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_01YGqBWgKfcNB9SmAP4iHddv): {"assignees":[{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwOTUyOTQ4","login":"SilvioBaratto","name":"Silvio Angelo Baratto Roldan","databaseId":0}],"body":"## Goal\nAdd a live WC2026 adapter that reuses the existing `FootballClient` to pull current standings, played results, and remaining group fixtures from football-data.org, normalizes team names through the crosswalk, and exposes a single \"state of the tournament as of today\" object. The API key is optional (live state only); everything degrades to no-key behavior already handled by `FootballClient`.\n\n## Context\n**Data contract (verified 2026-06-23, football-data.org v4, header `X-Auth-Token`, 10 req/min):**\n- `GET /v4/competitions/WC/matches` → `{... matches[]}` — currently **104 matches, 44 played** (mid group stage). Each match: `id, utcDate, status, stage, group, homeTeam{id,name}, awayTeam{id,name}, score{winner, fullTime{home,away}}`.\n  - `status` ∈ `FINISHED | IN_PLAY | PAUSED | TIMED | SCHEDULED`.\n  - `stage` ∈ `GROUP_STAGE | LAST_32 | LAST_16 | QUARTER_FINALS | SEMI_FINALS | THIRD_PLACE | FINAL` (counts 72/16/8/4/2/1/1). `LAST_32` = Round of 32.\n  - `group` ∈ `GROUP_A … GROUP_L` (12 groups) or `null` for knockouts.\n  - `score.winner` ∈ `HOME_TEAM | AWAY_TEAM | DRAW | null`; `fullTime.home/away` are `null` until played.\n  - **Knockout slot teams are `null`** (`homeTeam.name == null`) until groups resolve — do **not** expect the bracket from the API.\n- `GET /v4/competitions/WC/standings` → `{standings:[{stage,type,group,table[]}]}`, **12 groups**. Each `table[]` row: `position, team{id,name}, playedGames, won, draw, lost, points, goalsFor, goalsAgainst, goalDifference`.\n\n**Reuse, don't rebuild:** `FootballClient.get(path, params) -> dict` (in `worldcup_playoff/data/client.py`) already handles rate limiting (6 s spacing), circuit breaker, session resets, and reads `FOOTBALL_DATA_API_KEY` from env — works unauthenticated. Construct/accept it exactly like `BracketBuilder` / `generate_bracket_toml` (pass a client; the module-level factory default-constructs `FootballClient(ClientConfig())` when `client is None`).\n\nConventions: module `\"\"\"docstring\"\"\"` → `from __future__ import annotations` → `logger`; Pydantic value objects with `ConfigDict(extra=\"ignore\")`; small pure helper methods (< 10 lines). Every team name passes through `normalize_team` from the crosswalk so live results join martj42 history.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `LiveTournamentAdapter(client, competition=\"WC\")` with `fetch_matches() -> list[LiveMatch]`, `fetch_standings() -> list[GroupStanding]`, `tournament_state() -> TournamentState`\n- [ ] `tournament_state()` partitions group-stage matches into `played` vs `remaining_group_fixtures` (by `status`) and carries the 12-group `standings`\n- [ ] Knockout matches with `null` teams parse to `home_team is None` / `away_team is None` (no crash); all non-null names pass through `normalize_team`\n- [ ] Pydantic value objects `LiveMatch`, `GroupStanding`, `TournamentState` with `ConfigDict(extra=\"ignore\")`\n- [ ] Module-level `fetch_tournament_state(client=None, competition=\"WC\")` default-constructs `FootballClient` when none is passed\n- [ ] `LiveConfig` added to `config.py` and composed onto `AppConfig`; new symbols exported from `worldcup_playoff/data/__init__.py` + `__all__`\n- [ ] Tests mock the client (`MagicMock().get.side_effect = [matches_json, standings_json]`) with shape-accurate fixtures (a finished `GROUP_STAGE` match, a scheduled `GROUP_STAGE` match, a `LAST_32` match with null teams, a 12-group standings stub) — no real HTTP; the existing 250-test suite stays green\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #1: feat: team-name crosswalk for martj42 ↔ football-data.org normalization\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/data/live.py` — Pydantic `LiveMatch`/`GroupStanding`/`TournamentState`; `LiveTournamentAdapter` with private `_parse_match`, `_parse_standings`, `_split_played_remaining` (partition by `status`, scope the \"remaining group fixtures\" bucket to `stage == \"GROUP_STAGE\"`); module-level `fetch_tournament_state` factory.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_live.py` — follow the `test_bracket_builder.py` `_mock_client` pattern (a `MagicMock` client whose `.get` returns the fixture dicts); assert the 104/44 partition logic on a small representative fixture, null-team handling, 12-group parse, and crosswalk normalization. Patch `time.sleep` only if a real `FootballClient` is exercised (unnecessary with a `MagicMock` client).\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/config.py` — add `LiveConfig(BaseModel)` (`competition: str = \"WC\"`) and wire `live: LiveConfig = LiveConfig()` onto `AppConfig`.\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/data/__init__.py` — export `LiveTournamentAdapter`, `fetch_tournament_state`, `TournamentState`, `LiveMatch`, `GroupStanding`; extend `__all__`.\n- Add **no** new HTTP code — all network goes through `FootballClient`. Keep `live.py` free of any import from the bracket-slotting module to avoid cycles.","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIFtA","name":"priority:medium","description":"Medium priority","color":"FBCA04"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopII0g","name":"phase:implement","description":"Phase: implement","color":"D4C5F9"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIKMQ","name":"agent:python-pro","description":"Agent: python-pro","color":"7057FF"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopKxrQ","name":"area:data","description":"Area: data","color":"0052CC"}],"milestone":{"number":1,"title":"Cycle 1 — Data Loaders & Normalization","description":"Load martj42 CC0 international results (no-key primary source); live WC2026 adapter for football-data.org standings/results/fixtures; team-name normalization crosswalk (martj42 ↔ API); WC2026 Round-of-32 bracket-slotting rules (top 2 per group + 8 best 3rds → knockout template). Verify exact schemas match the data contracts (49,477 martj42 rows, 104 WC2026 matches). All loaders must be no-key by default (key optional for live state only).","dueOn":null},"state":"OPEN","title":"feat: live WC2026 adapter over FootballClient (matches, standings, tournament state)"}
